				<div class="para-cont-abt">
					<p>
						While eating vegan is defined as consuming only a plant based diet that doesn’t always mean that a snack labeled “vegan” is healthy. Technically an Oreo cookie is vegan but that doesn’t mean they are good for you. There are some easy rules to follow to make the most out of a whole food plant based diet. Here’s our short list:
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="process-main-abt">
					<div class="process-left-abt">
						<div class="inner-process-left">
							<h1>1.Eat organic. </h1>
							<p>
								Do we really need to explain why? Less chemicals healthier food. All our ingredients are organic.
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="inner-process-left">
							<h1> 2.Try not to cook foods over approximately
							118 degrees. </h1>
							<p>
								Heat kills enzymes and minerals. The hotter and longer you cook your food the less nutrition you’ll find in it. We dehydrate all our snacks below 118 degrees to maximize the minerals and enzymes in every bite.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="process-right-abt">
						<div class="inner-process-left">
							<h1>3. Soak seeds and nuts. </h1>
							<p>
								By soaking seeds and nuts in water it removes the enzyme inhibitor making them far easier to digest. No flavor is lost and your body makes better use of the nutrients. Yep we do this too.
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="inner-process-left">
							<h1>4. Eat the rainbow.</h1>
							<p>
								The more colors you have on your plate the more nutrients you’re getting. And remember the center of the rainbow is green. You can never go wrong incorporating green whole foods into your meals and snacks. Have you tried our kale?
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

